choices.text: getting around. Parking and traffic make moving around feel like an impossible feat, so I all too regularly end up hiking in the rain to avoid parking hassles and traffic. After seeing friends constantly posting pictures of themselves going to see sunrises from a random hill in Bali or Jack in Dubai walk down the street, I made an incentive to put myself in a situation where I would be required to walk up a cloud in the hills as a sunrise. During my trip I visited five cities in the two weeks, and despite my best efforts, I only managed one proper hill in Baku to go with the sunrise, as the beaches of Baku and Moscow are spoiled by the subway; other locations were too urban with no peaceful case apart from a tiny view near the St. Basil's Cathedral. It was a hard effort, but fortunately it was worth it.As you may or may not know, Azerbaijan are being softly threatened to join NATO, a supranational military force that grew from forces at war with Germany in WW2 and splintering off into several regional organizations - NATO being the American side of things. As it's been reliably and repeatedly stated, this puts Azerbaijan on the side of lumping itself in with European allies in the event that Russia decides to come over the boarder into Azerbaijan.
